{"meeting_datetime": "2004-01-29T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HTA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/hta12hb1177a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-01-29T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HTA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/hta12hb1177a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-02-02T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/hou14hb1177a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-02-02T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/hou14hb1177a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-02-02T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/hou14hb1177a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-02-06T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "STA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sta18hb1177a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-02-06T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "STA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sta18hb1177a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-02-06T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "STA", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sta18hb1177a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-02-10T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "S", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sen21hb1177a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-02-10T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "S", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sen21hb1177a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2004-02-10T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "S", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2004/sen21hb1177a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 18659, "bill_version_id": 99550, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2004-01-22T08:58:26-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to repeal certain provisions prohibiting certain government purchases. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 5-18-2.1 be repealed. 5-18-2.1. No public corporation may purchase any goods or services from any retailer that meets the definition of a retailer or a retailer maintaining a place of business in the state, pursuant to subdivisions 10-46-1(8) and (9), if the retailer or any affiliate of the retailer fails or refuses to collect and remit the sales and use tax on any sale delivered by any means to a location within this state. The Department of Revenue shall provide a list to public corporations of any retailer that fails to collect and remit the sales and use tax. For the purposes of this section, the term, affiliate, is any person who directly or indirectly owns or controls, is owned or controlled by, or is under common ownership or control with, another person. No public corporation is liable for the breach of any duty required of the public corporation by the provisions of this section if the breach, error, act, or omission is made in good faith. The provisions of this section do not apply to any emergency purchase made pursuant to \u00a7 5-18-3.1, or to any purchase made pursuant to \u00a7 5-18-18.1, 5-18-18.2, or 5-18-9.4, or to any contract for the construction of a new building or the remodeling or addition to an existing building or a contract for any other public improvement which involves the expenditure of twenty-five thousand dollars or more made pursuant to \u00a7 5-18-3."}, {"bill_id": 18659, "bill_version_id": 100244, "bill_version": "House Taxation Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2004-01-29T13:10:25-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to repeal certain provisions prohibiting certain government purchases and to declare an emergency. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 5-18-2.1 be repealed. 5-18-2.1. No public corporation may purchase any goods or services from any retailer that meets the definition of a retailer or a retailer maintaining a place of business in the state, pursuant to subdivisions 10-46-1(8) and (9), if the retailer or any affiliate of the retailer fails or refuses to collect and remit the sales and use tax on any sale delivered by any means to a location within this state. The Department of Revenue shall provide a list to public corporations of any retailer that fails to collect and remit the sales and use tax. For the purposes of this section, the term, affiliate, is any person who directly or indirectly owns or controls, is owned or controlled by, or is under common ownership or control with, another person. No public corporation is liable for the breach of any duty required of the public corporation by the provisions of this section if the breach, error, act, or omission is made in good faith. The provisions of this section do not apply to any emergency purchase made pursuant to \u00a7 5-18-3.1, or to any purchase made pursuant to \u00a7 5-18-18.1, 5-18-18.2, or 5-18-9.4, or to any contract for the construction of a new building or the remodeling or addition to an existing building or a contract for any other public improvement which involves the expenditure of twenty-five thousand dollars or more made pursuant to \u00a7 5-18-3. Section 2. Whereas, this Act is necessary for the support of the state government and its existing public institutions, an emergency is hereby declared to exist, and this Act shall be in full force and effect from and after its passage and approval."}, {"bill_id": 18659, "bill_version_id": 101129, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2004-02-11T09:51:40-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 18659, "action_date": "2004-01-22T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 99669, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/99669.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 157, "committee_id_action": 831, "committee_id_assigned": 827, "result": "N", "